A '''Very Important Person''' is a person who is accorded special privileges due to the status or importance of the person. The term "VIP" (usually pronouced V-I-P) is often used as an abbreviation for Very Important Person.

Such a person might be a [[celebrity]], a [[Head of State]], a [[High roller]], a [[politician]], a [[corporate officer]], a [[wealthy]] person, or any other person who receives special treatment for any reason. In some cases, such as [[ticket]]s to events, "VIP" status can be purchased by anyone.